%% Diagram: HTTP/2 vs HTTP/3 head-of-line blocking under packet loss
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    participant C as Client
    participant N as Network (1% loss)
    participant S as Server

    Note over C,S: HTTP/2 over TCP — single TCP stream, app-level multiplex
    C->>N: GET /a (stream 1) + GET /b (stream 3) + GET /c (stream 5)
    N-->>S: packets for /a, /b, /c
    S-->>N: response packets (interleaved)
    Note over N: Packet for /a is lost
    N--xC: packet loss on stream 1
    Note over C: TCP waits for retransmit — /b and /c are BLOCKED
    N-->>C: retransmit /a packet
    N-->>C: /a, /b, /c released together

    Note over C,S: HTTP/3 over QUIC — independent streams in transport
    C->>N: GET /a (stream 1) + GET /b (stream 5) + GET /c (stream 9)
    N-->>S: QUIC packets per stream
    S-->>N: response frames per stream
    Note over N: Packet for /a is lost
    N--xC: packet loss on stream 1
    N-->>C: /b and /c continue uninterrupted
    N-->>C: retransmit /a frame — /a delivered later
